What is loop in Java.
A loop in java is a process to control structure used to execute a block of code repeatedly
as long as a specified condition is true.

why use loop ?
1.To avoid writing repeated statements.
2.To process data in bulk (like array,string,objects etc..).
3.To perform repetitive task until a certain condition is met.

Type of loop in java.
for loop :- Used when the number of iteration is known.
while loop :- Used when the number of iteration depends of any specific condition.
do while :- Used when the one time iteration is necessary even if condition is false.

3 state of loop.
1.initial state. (initialization)
2.Condition state.
3.increament/decrement.

for (int i=0 ; i<10 ; i++){

    System.out.println("Hello")
    System.out.println("Bye")

}

